What is Availability? - It araise a point of SLA

. Reliability: Reliable hardware
. Recoverability: Because there may be many choices for recovering from a failure
. Timely error detection: If a component in your architecture fails, then fast detection is essential to recover from the        unexpected failure. 
. Continuous operation: Providing the ability for continuous access to your data is essential when very little or no downtime is acceptable to perform maintenance activities

->ITIL 

●  Service Strategy
●  Service Design
●  Service Transition
●  Service Operation
●  Continual Service Improvement.


->PATCHING

debian:
sudo apt-get update       # Fetches the list of available updates
sudo apt-get upgrade       # Strictly upgrades the current packages
sudo apt-get dist-upgrade     # Installs updates (new ones)

Redhat: 
yum check-update           # To check for the list of available updates
yum update                      # Installs updates for all the packages

 /etc/yun.repos.d/example.repo
[base]
name=CentOS-$releasever - Base
mirrorlist=http://mirrorlist.centos.org/?release=$releasever&arch=$basearch&repo=os
#baseurl=http://mirror.centos.org/centos/$releasever/os/$basearch/
gpgcheck=1
gpgkey=file:///etc/pki/rpm-gpg/RPM-GPG-KEY-CentOS-7

Difference between RPM and YUM
1. RPM is a package manager while YUM is a frontend that can be used with RPM.
2. The RPM package manager is unable to track dependencies while YUM can.

repoquery --list package_name
yumdb info yum
 
Yum list kernal|package|available|installed
yum deplist nfs-utils

-> Update kernal
	yum update kernel
        yum install kernel-{version}


